main event: A civilian pilot and Air Force reserve lieutenant observed a white, circular object that maneuvered erratically across the sky over Chicago, Illinois in 1932.
interesting points: The object displayed no lights, wings, or propulsion system, and moved silently at a speed much greater than conventional aircraft.
The object appeared to fade out for several seconds before reappearing.
The object changed direction abruptly a number of times during the 2-3 minute observation.
Weather conditions at the time included 1 scattered cloud cover, 15 miles visibility, and winds ranging from 13 knots at the surface to 40 knots at 30,000 feet.
No unusual meteorological, astronomical, or other activity was reported in the area at the time.
witnesses: a civilian pilot and Air Force reserve lieutenant
